  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network, it is generally not required to keep mobile data \"ON\" for making or receiving calls, especially if you are using the standard voice calling feature (VoLTE). Jio primarily utilizes Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology, which allows voice calls to be made over the 4G LTE network. \n\nHowever, if you are using a JioPhone or Jio's services that require the Jio 4G network, having data on can sometimes improve call quality or enable additional features, such as video calling or using the JioCall app. For regular voice calls, you do not need to keep your data turned on. \n\nIt's always good to check for any specific instructions from Jio itself, as network requirements can sometimes change.",
